    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it just doesn't feel internal. i've been looking into how neuromarketing works and how they're using brain-computer interfaces and binaural beats to influence people. what if they aren't just showing ads, but actually using frequency-based tech to target people's sleep cycles? it would explain why it feels so much like an invasion. if a company had that kind of tech, wouldn't they use it to get into people's heads while they're most vulnerable? i feel like i'm being experimented on.",
